Representational state transfer - Application Programming Interface
    It is a way for two application to interact with each other through internet using HTTP

Uses url to access data
Uses HTTP method (GET, PUT, POST, DELETE)
Usually send and recieve JSON data


Why do we use REST API?
    Because it is:
      ✅ Simple – Uses HTTP
      ✅ Fast – Lightweight JSON data
      ✅ Scalable – Works well for large systems
      ✅ Platform independent – Any language can use it
      ✅ Stateless – Each request is independent

REST API = communication bridge between systems

------------------------------------------------------------------------------- RESTfull api ----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Rest
  Representational State Transfer
  It is a set of rules/styles designing how two application to communicate over internet usually between a client(Browser, mobile app) and a server

Note
  It is not a Language or Framework
  It is an architecture style.

RestFull api
  API that follows the REST rules
  API designed using rest priniciples

REST rules make APIs simple, scalable, and predictable.
